WEBVTT

00:02.945 --> 00:04.883
It was my friend Abed's birthday.

00:04.897 --> 00:06.465
I had met Abed at community college

00:06.466 --> 00:07.922
almost two years earlier.

00:07.923 --> 00:09.386
His obsession with pop culture

00:09.387 --> 00:11.087
had always alienated him.

00:11.088 --> 00:13.733
He'd quote movies, pretend
his life was a TV show.

00:13.734 --> 00:15.039
He watched Cougar Town.

00:15.040 --> 00:17.476
It was as if he didn't
want people to like him.

00:17.796 --> 00:19.911
Then this year, around Christmas,

00:19.912 --> 00:21.167
he had some kind of...

00:21.168 --> 00:23.457
I don't know... mental episode,

00:23.458 --> 00:25.900
saying people were made
of clay... stuff like that.

00:26.267 --> 00:28.524
He'd seemed okay since,
but when I asked him

00:28.525 --> 00:30.304
if he'd like to do
anything for his birthday,

00:30.305 --> 00:32.619
he told me we should have
dinner, just he and I,

00:32.621 --> 00:35.097
for an important conversation.

00:35.098 --> 00:36.631
It made me nervous.

00:37.277 --> 00:39.840
The restaurant Abed had chosen
wasn't his style at all.

00:39.841 --> 00:42.177
There were cloth napkins, no TVs.

00:42.260 --> 00:44.364
Abed liked chicken fingers, video games,

00:44.365 --> 00:45.891
Quentin Tarantino.

00:47.868 --> 00:49.587
Babysitting him through a full meal

00:49.588 --> 00:51.261
at a restaurant for grown-ups...

00:51.823 --> 00:53.718
I just wasn't up for it.

00:54.254 --> 00:56.714
But I loved Abed. Everyone did.

00:56.908 --> 00:59.385
So I had come there with a
surprise plan of my own.

00:59.386 --> 01:01.725
Hey, uh, could I get a MacAllan, neat?

01:04.099 --> 01:05.331
Jeffrey!

01:07.712 --> 01:08.884
Buddy.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.162
I like your sweater.

01:14.225 --> 01:16.078
Did it come with a Golden Retriever?

01:16.788 --> 01:18.263
You look good too.

01:20.693 --> 01:23.354
I would like a, uh... spritzer.

01:23.355 --> 01:25.126
Abed was being weird.

01:25.127 --> 01:28.522
And by that, I mean he wasn't being weird.

01:28.667 --> 01:31.744
He was hugging, smiling,
making eye contact,

01:31.745 --> 01:34.986
and in 30 seconds, he hadn't
made a reference to anything.

01:35.418 --> 01:37.280
I had come in worried about him,

01:37.281 --> 01:38.964
thinking he needed help.

01:38.965 --> 01:41.984
But seeing him like this made
me more worried than ever.

01:42.018 --> 01:45.060
Get it? Like Pulp Fiction.

01:45.889 --> 01:47.522
It's a wallet that says "Bad mother..."

01:47.523 --> 01:49.202
- Your table's ready, gentlemen.
- Thank you.

01:49.203 --> 01:51.131
Actually, uh, I had an idea.

01:51.369 --> 01:53.604
I saw a very cool burger place
just a few...

01:53.605 --> 01:56.382
Nonsense.
I didn't come downtown for burgers.

01:56.383 --> 01:57.737
Come, come.

01:58.922 --> 02:00.829
Uh, I-I'll be right there.

02:07.313 --> 02:09.145
Hey, uh, we're running a little bit late...

02:09.145 --> 02:11.387
No big deal, just a small speed bump.

02:11.578 --> 02:13.420
Well, hurry up. We're waiting.

02:14.475 --> 02:16.320
Surprise!

02:16.321 --> 02:19.585
Guys, no! They're running late.

02:20.765 --> 02:23.130
That was Jeff.
He says there's some kind of speed bump.

02:24.380 --> 02:26.063
Pierce, nobody can hear you.

02:26.775 --> 02:29.347
Well, I'm hot, and my balls
are touching the zipper!

